The paper deals with speaker feature learning using deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of speech processing and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of convolutional and time-delay neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as speech recognition and language modeling, hence cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques for feature learning, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of information leakage in the current model, which could also be relevant to the sub-category of security and privacy (cs.SDQ).
